te, a decision will follow within 90 days.</li></ul><p>If you are admitted to the insurance, you will be insured for 10 years from the date the Flemish Housing Fund received your application. You will be sent a policy by the insurer. It explains what you must do if you become involuntarily unemployed or disabled. So keep this document carefully.</p><h3>Intervention</h3><p>If you are insured and you fall out of work, you can apply for an allowance:</p><ul><li>A <strong>waiting period of 3 months</strong> applies from the time you apply. You can only get a loan repayment allowance if you can prove that you have been continuously disabled or involuntarily and fully unemployed for at least 3 months.</li><li>The relief does not work retrospectively. So you will not get a concession for the waiting period.</li></ul><p>All the information to apply for a <strong>relief</strong> can be found in the insurance policy you received from Ethias. You can also contact Ethias.</p><h3>Refinancing</h3><p>If you <strong>refinance</strong>, the insurance you already had will continue as normal. You do not have to do anything.</p><p>If you had not yet applied for guaranteed living insurance for your loan, you can no longer get it when you refinance that loan either.</p><ul></ul>","en":"<h3>Application of the insurance</h3><p>Please <a href=\"https://www.vlaamswoningfonds.be/onze-diensten/verzekering-gewaarborgd-wonen\">apply for the Guaranteed Housing Insurance online</a> (only in Dutch) within the year after the first withdrawal of capital from your mortgage.</p><h3>Application of the contribution</h3><p>Apply for the contribution with Ethias insurance company.</p><p>After the application and a three-month waiting period you may receive a contribution towards the payment of your mortgage for a maximum of three years. To this end you must be able to prove that you are incapable of work or involuntarily and fully unemployed.</p><ul></ul>","de":"<h3>Versicherungsantrag</h3><p>Stellen Sie d